ntaining `session:expiry` ZSET\n  Line 103: - Automatic expiration handled by Redis\n  Line 118: - True atomic execution on Redis server\n  Line 120: - More \"Redis-native\" approach\n  Line 127: **Decision**: Use Redis pipelines for better code clarity and easier testing.\n  Line 133: ### Redis Store Structure\n  Line 155: func makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n  Line 180: | Method | Redis Commands | Notes |\n  Line 190: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` | Close Redis connection |\n  Line 223: 1. **TestRedisStore_Ping_Success**: Mock `PING` returns `PONG`\n  Line 224: 2. **TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound**: Mock `GET` returns `nil`\n  Line 225: 3. **TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected**: Validate input validation\n  Line 226: 4. **TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success**: Verify pipeline commands\n  Line 227: 5. **TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey**: Verify `SET XX` behavior\n  Line 228: 6. **TestRedisStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_Success**: Verify cleanup\n  Line 229: 7. **TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_Empty**: Limit <= 0 returns nil\n  Line 230: 8. **TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound**: Missing session\n  Line 234: 1. **TestRedisStore_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full CRUD operations with real Redis\n  Line 235: 2. **TestRedisStore_Integration_ConcurrentAccess**: Concurrent store/update/delete\n  Line 236: 3. **TestRedisStore_Integration_IndexConsistency**: Verify ZSET consistency after operations\n  Line 237: 4. **TestRedisStore_Integration_PasswordAuth**: Test with password authentication\n  Line 242: func newTestRedisStore() (*redisStore, func()) {\n  Line 243:     // Use testcontainers-go or dockertest for Redis container\n  Line 257: - [ ] `makeRedisOptions()` validates required fields\n  Line 259: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Redis instance\n  Line 270: - Redis Client Docs: https://github.com/redis/go-redis\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_2026041